# Top bar components

Playground provides two top bars. **Never** recreate an admin or user portal top bar from scratch when one of these matches the design.

| Component | File | Use when |
|---|---|---|
| **AdminTopBar** | `src/components/AdminTopBar.vue` | Admin console: search, shortcut tag, icon actions, AI assistant |
| **UserTopBar** | `src/components/UserTopBar.vue` | User portal: thin bar with external links (e.g. Launch Admin Portal, Learn more) |

## AdminTopBar

### Import

```typescript
import AdminTopBar from '@/components/AdminTopBar.vue';
```

### Default behavior

- **AI Search icon** (`AiSearchIcon` from `@jumpcloud/icons`)
- **Search placeholder**: `"Search User, Devices, Apps, etc..."`
- **Shortcut tag**: `"⌘/Ctrl + K"`
- **Four icon buttons** (Customer Support, Lifebuoy, Flag, Checklist)
- **AI Assistant** (`AiAgentButton` from Circuit DS)

```html
<AdminTopBar />
```

### Usage by page type

| Page type | Variant | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Main/root pages | Default — no back button | `<AdminTopBar />` |
| Nested/detail pages | With back button | `<AdminTopBar showBackButton backButtonLabel="Devices" @back="router.back()" />` |

**Rules:**

- The back button MUST navigate to the previous page (`router.back()` or equivalent). Never use it for unrelated actions.
- `backButtonLabel` should match the previous page title when known; otherwise `"Back"`.

### Props (AdminTopBar)

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `searchPlaceholder` | `string` | `'Search User, Devices, Apps, etc...'` | Placeholder in the search area |
| `shortcutLabel` | `string` | `'⌘/Ctrl + K'` | Shortcut shown as a Tag |
| `showSearchIcon` | `boolean` | `true` | Toggle AI search icon |
| `iconButtons` | `AdminTopBarIconButton[]` | 4 defaults | Custom icon buttons |
| `showBackButton` | `boolean` | `false` | Back button + divider |
| `backButtonLabel` | `string` | `'Back'` | Back button label |

### AdminTopBarIconButton

```typescript
interface AdminTopBarIconButton {
  icon: Component;
  label: string;
  onClick?: () => void;
}
```

### Events (AdminTopBar)

| Event | Payload | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `search-click` | — | Search area clicked |
| `icon-button-click` | `label: string` | Icon button clicked |
| `ai-assistant-click` | `event: Event` | AI Assistant clicked |
| `back` | — | Back clicked when `showBackButton` |

### Slots (AdminTopBar)

| Slot | Description |
|---|---|
| `search-icon` | Replace default AI search icon |
| `icon-buttons` | Replace all default icon buttons |

### Page layout (admin)

Place `AdminTopBar` as the first child in the main column after `AppNavigation`:

```html
<div class="flex h-screen overflow-hidden">
  <AppNavigation ... />
  <div class="flex-1 flex flex-col min-w-0 overflow-auto">
    <AdminTopBar />
    <PageHeader title="Devices" />
  </div>
</div>
```

### Figma detection (admin)

Use **AdminTopBar** when the bar includes search + shortcut tag + AI assistant / icon cluster. Use **back** variant when the design shows a back control with divider on the left.

