## UserTopBar

### Import

```typescript
import UserTopBar from '@/components/UserTopBar.vue';
```

### Behavior

Right-aligned `LinkText` links with external-link icon (`showIcon`), `target="_blank"`, `rel="noopener noreferrer"`. Default labels: **Launch Admin Portal**, **Learn more**.

```html
<UserTopBar
  adminPortalHref="https://console.example.com"
  learnMoreHref="https://docs.example.com"
/>
```

### Props (UserTopBar)

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `adminPortalHref` | `string` | `'#'` | Admin portal URL |
| `learnMoreHref` | `string` | `'#'` | Learn-more URL |
| `adminPortalLabel` | `string` | `'Launch Admin Portal'` | First link label |
| `learnMoreLabel` | `string` | `'Learn more'` | Second link label |

### Page layout (user portal)

Same position as admin bar: first row in the main column after `AppNavigation`.

### Figma detection (user)

Use **UserTopBar** when the bar is a thin strip with text links and external-link icons only (no search, no AI button).
